%N A398010 Decimal expansion of Sum_{k>=1} d(k)^2 * log(k) / k^2, where d(k) is the number of divisors of k (A000005).
%H A398010 Matthew Perkins and Robert A. Van Gorder, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/s11139-018-0037-4">Closed-form calculation of infinite products of Glaisher-type related to Dirichlet series</a>, The Ramanujan Journal, Vol. 49, No. 2 (2019), pp. 371-389. See p. 377, Corollary 2.4.
%F A398010 Equals (5*Pi^4/36) * (24 * log(A) + 120*log(A_3) - log(2*Pi) - gamma), where gamma is Euler's constant (A001620), A is the Glaisher-Kinkelin constant (A074962), and A_3 is the third Bendersky constant (A243263).
%e A398010 14.56065980468059403966902833396791177087987838845236...
%t A398010 RealDigits[(5*Pi^4/36) * (24 * Log[Glaisher] - 120*Zeta'[-3] - Log[2*Pi] - EulerGamma - 11/6), 10, 120][[1]]
%o A398010 (PARI) (5*Pi^4/36) * (1/6 - 24*zeta'(-1) - 120*zeta'(-3) - log(2*Pi) - Euler)
%Y A398010 Cf. A000005, A001620, A035116, A073002 (Sum_{k>=1} log(k)/k^2), A074962, A258945 (conjecturally (1/100)*Sum_{k>=1} d(k)^2/k^2), A243263, A398008, A398009.
